Basically, with freedom becomes the responsibility of self regulation and of warning others about moral issues.
Without this, the front page of ZeroMe would be full of spammers, CP and gore.
Just thinking that, because you are free, it means you should do everything you please, is to be a Libertine with no moral values.
And if people aren't regulated by themselves with moral values, the libertinism of that Freedom will not save them, but rather destroy them.
Just think that, if people here did not know better, we'd just be spamming disgusting shit on the front page. And if somebody did it, nobody would care, because we'd have no Moral compass.
We also have the freedom to criticize certain behaviors, as freedom goes both ways. Some people are under the impression that, because they CAN do something, it means they SHOULD do it, and that nobody can say a thing about it, otherwise it is Censorship. So do we have the freedom to talk about immoral behavior that we dislike and disapprove, and to boycott it as possible.
Not only that, if we want this place to be functional, we also have the responsibility to criticize some sorts of behavior and to not allow this to be a place of disorder and disgraceful content.

Who hates you will tell you to do as you please.
Who loves you will tell you to take care.
